headline: Barclays downgrades Texas Instruments on China risk, demand concerns
summary: Investing.com -- Barclays downgraded Texas Instruments (NASDAQ:TXN) to "Underweight" from "Equal Weight" and cut its price target to $125 amid growing risks tied to U.S.-China trade tensions, rising production costs, and weakening demand in key end markets.
